cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SE 

The paper deals with the detection of anomalous activities in blockchain-based systems, which is a security issue. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the use of distributed systems, which suggests the category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of meta-data and behavioral data implies the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions complexity analysis, which suggests the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions the privacy of the solution, which suggests the category cs.SE (Software Engineering).
